  %article{:class => "jFlickery"}
    %header
      %h3 jFlickery
      %a [+]
    %p jFlickery is a Flickr API wrapper in vanilla JavaScript. Currently it covers PhotoSets - getList (listing of photosets) and getPhotos (photos from a particular photoset).
    %footer

  %article{:class => "matterhorn"}
    %header
      %h3 Matterhorn
      %a [+]
    %p Matterhorn is a Free, Open Source project for Lecture Capture & Video Management for Education. It is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution 3.0 United States License and the source is available under Educational Community License 2.0. I am a committer on this project.
    %footer

  %article{:class => "sakai"}
    %header
      %h3 Sakai
      %a [+]
    %p Sakai is a vibrant community creating technology that enhances teaching, learning and research. It is a community of educators collaborating to create open software.
    %footer

  %article{:class => "dexter"}
    %header
      %h3 dexter
      %a [+]
    %p dexter is a simple HTML5 canvas experiment. It will form the basis for my HTML5 Canvas library animation.js.
    %footer

  %article{:class => "peekaboo"}
    %header
      %h3 peekaboo
      %a [+]
    %p peekaboo is a toy application for exploring the wonders of redis and text to speech synthesis.
    %footer

